        <hl1>Dollar Differential</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In his article "Americans in a Land of Opportunity: Europe"  [ July 2 ] , Alan Riding neglects to explain why young American writers and painters no longer go to Europe to develop as artists. Besides the growing insularity of Americans in general, surely the main reason for this is economic, i.e., the weak dollar.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In his article "Americans in a Land of Opportunity: Europe"  [ July 2 ] , Alan Riding neglects to explain why young American writers and painters no longer go to Europe to develop as artists. Besides the growing insularity of Americans in general, surely the main reason for this is economic, i.e., the weak dollar.</p>
        <p>When I went to Paris in 1948 to write a book, I lived for $75 a month, eating all my meals in restaurants and going to the opera every week. It was the biggest bargain of my generation, and artists and writers particularly took full advantage of the situation.  EDWARD FIELD  New York  EXPATRIATES</p>
      </block>
